history.content: I took CS 288, and it was pretty time consuming (as someone with less experience) around deadlines. There were about 5 projects, each of which took me about maybe 20 hours to complete. For 288, I found a linear algebra background to be less important than just experience coding neural nets. I've also taken CS 189, and although it should be lighter in a non-Sahai semester, I would still expect it to take a huge chunk of time since the material is pretty tough even with a good background. I've heard CS 182 is lighter than the other two, but still requires some time commitment, so I would be cautious taking it with two heavier classes. Honestly if you feel ready enough to take CS 288 and have the research experience to back it up, I think CS 182 can wait. I know people who took Info 159, and I it teaches the most unique material compared to CS 182 and CS 288, so if I were you I would switch out one of those for 159.
